{"title_page": "Armenian National Congress", "text_new": "{{about|the modern-day political coalition|the 1917 assembly|Armenian National Congress (1917)}}\n{{update|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox Political party\n| name = Armenian National Congress\n|native_name = \u0540\u0561\u0575 \u0531\u0566\u0563\u0561\u0575\u056b\u0576 \u053f\u0578\u0576\u0563\u0580\u0565\u057d\n|logo = Anc logo.PNG\n|leader = [[Levon Ter-Petrosyan]]\n|foundation = 2008\n|predecessor= [[Pan-Armenian National Movement]]\n|membership = \n|ideology = [[Classical liberalism]]<br />[[Market liberalism]]<br />[[Pro-Europeanism|Soft Pro-Europeanism]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.armenianow.com/news/politics/26300/levon_terpetrosian_armenia_opposition|agency=ArmeniaNow|title=Ter-Petrosyan: Congress suggests following Constitution instead of preaching \"ethno-religious ideology\"|date=6 December 2010|accessdate=26 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anc.am/?page_id=1024|publisher=Armenian National Congress|title=Party Programs}}</ref>\n|position = [[Centrism|Centre]] to [[Centre-right politics|centre-right]]\n|european = [[ALDE Party]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aldeparty.eu/en/news/liberalism-armenia-well-rooted-among-anc-country-slippery-slope |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328125403/http://www.aldeparty.eu/en/news/liberalism-armenia-well-rooted-among-anc-country-slippery-slope |archive-date=2016-03-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|headquarters = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenia]]\n|website = http://www.anc.am/\n|colorcode = {{Armenian National Congress/meta/color}}\n|country = Armenia\n|seats1_title = [[National Assembly of Armenia|National Assembly]]\n|seats1 = {{Composition bar|0|132|hex={{Armenian National Congress/meta/color}}}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Armenian National Congress''' ({{lang-hy|italic=yes|\u0540\u0561\u0575 \u0531\u0566\u0563\u0561\u0575\u056b\u0576 \u053f\u0578\u0576\u0563\u0580\u0565\u057d, Hay Azgayin Kongres}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Armenia]], led by former President [[Levon Ter-Petrosyan]] and formed in 2008. Its direct predecessor was the [[Pan-Armenian National Movement]].\n\nIt is often abbreviated as '''\u0540\u0531\u053f''' or '''HAK''', in keeping with its Armenian spelling, but it is occasionally referred to as the '''ANC''' in [[English language|English-language]] media, including in its official website.\n\nFrom 2008 to 2013 it was a coalition of 13 opposition parties. In 2013, when certain member parties left the Pan-Armenian National Movement, the remainder of the organization collectively decided during a conference to form a new party called the Armenian National Congress.<ref>[https://armenpress.am/arm/news/707689/ ANC turns into Armenian National Congress party]</ref><ref>[http://news.am/arm/news/141736.html PANM becomes Armenian National Congress party]</ref>\n\n==Formation and goals==\nThe website of the Armenian National Congress lists five main goals:\n{{quote|text={{*}}The immediate release of all political prisoners.<br /> {{*}}Attaining complete freedom of speech, access to media, and assembly.<br /> {{*}}Truly independent investigation of the crimes of March 1 with the significant participation of International experts.<br /> {{*}}Initiation of a dialogue with the authorities about democratic reforms after the fulfillment of at least the first condition.<br /> {{*}}Holding of pre-term presidential and parliamentary elections.|sign=Armenian National Congress|source=official website<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anc.am/en/aboutANC/category19/|publisher=Armenian National Congress|title=Declaration on The Creation of the Armenian National Congress}}</ref>}}\n\nIn addition, the ANC also believes in maintaining good relations with Armenia's neighbors, including normalizing relations with both Turkey and Azerbaijan, developing closer relations with the [[Middle East]], self-determination of the [[Republic of Artsakh]], encouraging further [[European integration]] of Armenia and deepening cooperation with the [[European union]], the [[United States]], [[Russia]] and maintaining strong relations with [[Commonwealth of Independent States|CIS]] member states.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anc.am/?page_id=1024|publisher=Armenian National Congress|title=Party Programs}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2008 merge===\nThe [[Impeachment Union]] party was officially dissolved in 2008 as members opted to join the ANC.\n\n===2011 protests===\nDuring the [[2011 Armenian protests]], the HAK played a major role in organizing demonstrations and pushing for the government of President [[Serzh Sargsyan]], who defeated Ter-Petrosyan in the [[2008 Armenian presidential election|2008 election]], to accept the demands of protesters.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/90001/90777/90853/7345145.html|agency=People's Daily Online|title=Armenia's opposition ANC holds rally on Liberty Square again|date=9 April 2011|accessdate=25 April 2011}}</ref> The death of 10 supporters of Ter-Petrosyan as a result of [[2008 Armenian presidential election protests|protests]] that followed Sargsyan's disputed victory are a major rallying point for protesters.\n\nRelations between the HAK and [[Heritage (Armenia)|Heritage]], a fellow opposition party, have historically been rocky, with differences in tactics during the 2011 protests widening the rift.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/politics/news/66965/Stepan_Safaryan_urges_to_stop_HeritageANC_confrontation|agency=PanArmenian|date=12 April 2011|accessdate=25 April 2011|title=Stepan Safaryan urges to stop Heritage-ANC confrontation}}</ref>\n\n===2012 parliamentary election===\n{{main|2012 Armenian parliamentary election}}\nAfter the 2012 parliamentary elections Armenian National Congress gained 7 seats in the [[National Assembly of Armenia]].<ref>http://res.elections.am/images/doc/060512.pdf</ref>\n\n===2015 Armenian constitutional referendum===\n{{main|2015 Armenian constitutional referendum}}\nIn the 2015 constitutional referendum in Armenia, the ANC  supported the \"no\" camp. ANC leader Levon Ter-Petrosyan, stated that \"the constitutional changes initiated by [[Serzh Sargsyan]] was destroying the bases of the state\".<ref>[http://www.azatutyun.am/media/video/27260979.html \u053c\u0587\u0578\u0576 \u054f\u0565\u0580-\u054a\u0565\u057f\u0580\u0578\u057d\u0575\u0561\u0576. \u0546\u0578\u0580 \u054d\u0561\u0570\u0574\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0564\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0568 \u0584\u0561\u0576\u0564\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567 \u057a\u0565\u057f\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0570\u056b\u0574\u0584\u0565\u0580\u0568]</ref>\n\n===2017 Armenian parliamentary election===\n{{main|2017 Armenian parliamentary election}}\nThe ANC formed a [[political alliance]] with the [[People's Party of Armenia]], however the alliance failed to win any seats following the election.\n\n===2018 Armenian parliamentary election===\n{{main|2018 Armenian parliamentary election}}\nThe ANC did not participate in the 2018 Armenian parliamentary elections.\n\n==Recent activities==\n===2019===\nA statement from the Armenian National Congress in 2019 addressed tax reform: \"On 7 March 2019, the Government of the Republic of Armenia approved the package of draft amendments to the Tax Code and to several laws regulating tax relations, but certain draft laws will cause harm to the activities of small and medium enterprises.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.am/eng/news/502394.html|title=Armenian National Congress issues statement on Armenia government's tax reforms|website=news.am|language=en|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Politics}}\n* [[Programs of political parties in Armenia]]\n* [[Politics of Armenia]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.anc.am Official website of the Armenian National Congress]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Armenian Political Parties}}\n{{Alliance of Liberals and Democrats for Europe Party}}\n\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Alliance of Liberals and Democrats for Europe Party member parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Armenian democracy movements]]\n[[Category:Classical liberal parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Pro-European political parties]]\n[[Category:Pro-European political parties in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Liberal parties in Armenia]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the modern-day political coalition|the 1917 assembly|Armenian National Congress (1917)}}\n{{update|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox Political party\n| name = Armenian National Congress\n|native_name = \u0540\u0561\u0575 \u0531\u0566\u0563\u0561\u0575\u056b\u0576 \u053f\u0578\u0576\u0563\u0580\u0565\u057d\n|logo = ANCWebLogo.gif\n|leader = [[Levon Ter-Petrosyan]]\n|foundation = 2008\n|predecessor= [[Pan-Armenian National Movement]]\n|membership = \n|ideology = [[Classical liberalism]]<br />[[Market liberalism]]<br />[[Pro-Europeanism|Soft Pro-Europeanism]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.armenianow.com/news/politics/26300/levon_terpetrosian_armenia_opposition|agency=ArmeniaNow|title=Ter-Petrosyan: Congress suggests following Constitution instead of preaching \"ethno-religious ideology\"|date=6 December 2010|accessdate=26 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anc.am/?page_id=1024|publisher=Armenian National Congress|title=Party Programs}}</ref>\n|position = [[Centrism|Centre]] to [[Centre-right politics|centre-right]]\n|european = [[ALDE Party]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aldeparty.eu/en/news/liberalism-armenia-well-rooted-among-anc-country-slippery-slope |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328125403/http://www.aldeparty.eu/en/news/liberalism-armenia-well-rooted-among-anc-country-slippery-slope |archive-date=2016-03-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|headquarters = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenia]]\n|website = http://www.anc.am/\n|colorcode = {{Armenian National Congress/meta/color}}\n|country = Armenia\n|seats1_title = [[National Assembly of Armenia|National Assembly]]\n|seats1 = {{Composition bar|0|132|hex={{Armenian National Congress/meta/color}}}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Armenian National Congress''' ({{lang-hy|italic=yes|\u0540\u0561\u0575 \u0531\u0566\u0563\u0561\u0575\u056b\u0576 \u053f\u0578\u0576\u0563\u0580\u0565\u057d, Hay Azgayin Kongres}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Armenia]], led by former President [[Levon Ter-Petrosyan]] and formed in 2008. Its direct predecessor was the [[Pan-Armenian National Movement]].\n\nIt is often abbreviated as '''\u0540\u0531\u053f''' or '''HAK''', in keeping with its Armenian spelling, but it is occasionally referred to as the '''ANC''' in [[English language|English-language]] media, including in its official website.\n\nFrom 2008 to 2013 it was a coalition of 13 opposition parties. In 2013, when certain member parties left the Pan-Armenian National Movement, the remainder of the organization collectively decided during a conference to form a new party called the Armenian National Congress.<ref>[https://armenpress.am/arm/news/707689/ ANC turns into Armenian National Congress party]</ref><ref>[http://news.am/arm/news/141736.html PANM becomes Armenian National Congress party]</ref>\n\n==Formation and goals==\nThe website of the Armenian National Congress lists five main goals:\n{{quote|text={{*}}The immediate release of all political prisoners.<br /> {{*}}Attaining complete freedom of speech, access to media, and assembly.<br /> {{*}}Truly independent investigation of the crimes of March 1 with the significant participation of International experts.<br /> {{*}}Initiation of a dialogue with the authorities about democratic reforms after the fulfillment of at least the first condition.<br /> {{*}}Holding of pre-term presidential and parliamentary elections.|sign=Armenian National Congress|source=official website<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anc.am/en/aboutANC/category19/|publisher=Armenian National Congress|title=Declaration on The Creation of the Armenian National Congress}}</ref>}}\n\nIn addition, the ANC also believes in maintaining good relations with Armenia's neighbors, including normalizing relations with both Turkey and Azerbaijan, developing closer relations with the [[Middle East]], self-determination of the [[Republic of Artsakh]], encouraging further [[European integration]] of Armenia and deepening cooperation with the [[European union]], the [[United States]], [[Russia]] and maintaining strong relations with [[Commonwealth of Independent States|CIS]] member states.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anc.am/?page_id=1024|publisher=Armenian National Congress|title=Party Programs}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2008 merge===\nThe [[Impeachment Union]] party was officially dissolved in 2008 as members opted to join the ANC.\n\n===2011 protests===\nDuring the [[2011 Armenian protests]], the HAK played a major role in organizing demonstrations and pushing for the government of President [[Serzh Sargsyan]], who defeated Ter-Petrosyan in the [[2008 Armenian presidential election|2008 election]], to accept the demands of protesters.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/90001/90777/90853/7345145.html|agency=People's Daily Online|title=Armenia's opposition ANC holds rally on Liberty Square again|date=9 April 2011|accessdate=25 April 2011}}</ref> The death of 10 supporters of Ter-Petrosyan as a result of [[2008 Armenian presidential election protests|protests]] that followed Sargsyan's disputed victory are a major rallying point for protesters.\n\nRelations between the HAK and [[Heritage (Armenia)|Heritage]], a fellow opposition party, have historically been rocky, with differences in tactics during the 2011 protests widening the rift.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/politics/news/66965/Stepan_Safaryan_urges_to_stop_HeritageANC_confrontation|agency=PanArmenian|date=12 April 2011|accessdate=25 April 2011|title=Stepan Safaryan urges to stop Heritage-ANC confrontation}}</ref>\n\n===2012 parliamentary election===\n{{main|2012 Armenian parliamentary election}}\nAfter the 2012 parliamentary elections Armenian National Congress gained 7 seats in the [[National Assembly of Armenia]].<ref>http://res.elections.am/images/doc/060512.pdf</ref>\n\n===2015 Armenian constitutional referendum===\n{{main|2015 Armenian constitutional referendum}}\nIn the 2015 constitutional referendum in Armenia, the ANC  supported the \"no\" camp. ANC leader Levon Ter-Petrosyan, stated that \"the constitutional changes initiated by [[Serzh Sargsyan]] was destroying the bases of the state\".<ref>[http://www.azatutyun.am/media/video/27260979.html \u053c\u0587\u0578\u0576 \u054f\u0565\u0580-\u054a\u0565\u057f\u0580\u0578\u057d\u0575\u0561\u0576. \u0546\u0578\u0580 \u054d\u0561\u0570\u0574\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0564\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0568 \u0584\u0561\u0576\u0564\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567 \u057a\u0565\u057f\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0570\u056b\u0574\u0584\u0565\u0580\u0568]</ref>\n\n===2017 Armenian parliamentary election===\n{{main|2017 Armenian parliamentary election}}\nThe ANC formed a [[political alliance]] with the [[People's Party of Armenia]], however the alliance failed to win any seats following the election.\n\n===2018 Armenian parliamentary election===\n{{main|2018 Armenian parliamentary election}}\nThe ANC did not participate in the 2018 Armenian parliamentary elections.\n\n==Recent activities==\n===2019===\nA statement from the Armenian National Congress in 2019 addressed tax reform: \"On 7 March 2019, the Government of the Republic of Armenia approved the package of draft amendments to the Tax Code and to several laws regulating tax relations, but certain draft laws will cause harm to the activities of small and medium enterprises.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.am/eng/news/502394.html|title=Armenian National Congress issues statement on Armenia government's tax reforms|website=news.am|language=en|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Politics}}\n* [[Programs of political parties in Armenia]]\n* [[Politics of Armenia]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.anc.am Official website of the Armenian National Congress]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Armenian Political Parties}}\n{{Alliance of Liberals and Democrats for Europe Party}}\n\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Alliance of Liberals and Democrats for Europe Party member parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Armenian democracy movements]]\n[[Category:Classical liberal parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Pro-European political parties]]\n[[Category:Pro-European political parties in Armenia]]\n[[Category:Liberal parties in Armenia]]\n", "name_user": "Textfabrikant", "label": "safe", "comment": "+bigger and more compact logo, replaced gif with png", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armenian_National_Congress"}
